fields.title: Lessons
fields.content:
All lessons are designed to accommodate any age and swimming ability.

Private Lessons (30 minutes)

Private swim lesson are uniquely designed to maximize results. All teaching is focused solely on one student to work on areas of weakness and strengths. Private lessons have no other students to distract from teaching, which allows the lesson to progress at the student’s unique pace.

Semi-Private Lessons (30 minutes)

Semi-Private lessons are a two-student lessons that allows for divided attention to each student. These lessons provide a comfortable and encouraging environment by having the sibling or friend learning beside them. Even though the instructor divides attention to each student, each student is able to also watch and learn from the other.

Small Group (30 minutes)

Small Group lessons consist of three students. Instruction is divided between each of the students to provide for individual attention while still in a group environment. With a small group lesson, students are encouraged and gain confidence by watching other swimmers try various swimming skills first.

fields.title: Prices
fields.content:
Rates Per Lesson

Private $28 (1 student)
Semi Private $16/student (2 students)
Small Group $12/student (3 students)

Each lesson is priced by the number of students required for the type of lesson.
For example, in a Semi-Private lesson two students are required in order the the price to lower to $16/student. If you sign up for a Semi-Private lesson only registering one student-and if no additional student signs up-the lesson is considered a Private lesson and the Private lesson rate applies.



Payment

Payment for all lessons is due Monthly on your 1st lesson of the month.
If you have 4 lessons a month, payment is due on the 1st lesson for all 4 lessons in that month.

Payment Forms

Cash or Checks made out to: Sea Turtle Swim School
Payments will be placed in envelopes and deposited in the drop box located at the pool facility.

Refunds

There are ONLY refunds for classes canceled by the instructor. There are NO refunds, credit or make ups for missed classes. Missed classes by students include illnesses, vacations, forgotten lessons.

Trading, Giving Away or Selling Lesson

The lessons you pay for are yours to trade, give away or sell as you choose. Since there are NO refunds for missed lessons- you are welcome to make arrangements to sell, trade or give away the lessons you have paid for. If you are going to miss a lesson and have made arrangements for another student to take the lesson time, you are required to inform the instructor that you have done so.

fields.title: Rules
fields.content:
REFUNDS-

There are ONLY refunds for lessons canceled by the instructor. There are NO refunds, credit or make ups for missed lessons. Missed lessons by students include illnesses, vacations and forgotten lessons.

PAYMENT-

Payment for lessons is due monthly. Payment for all lessons scheduled for the month are due at the beginning of each month. If you have 4 lessons a month, payment is due at the first lesson for all 4 lessons in that month.

PAYMENT FORMS-

Cash or Checks made out to: Sea Turtle Swim School

BUYING/SELLING LESSONS-

The lessons you pay for are yours to trade, give away or sell as you choose. Since there are NO refunds for missed lessons- you are welcome to make arrangements to sell, trade or give away the lessons you have paid for. If you are going to miss a lesson and have made arrangements for another student to take the lesson time, you are required to inform the instructor that you have done so.

DISCONTINUING LESSONS–

If you wish to stop lessons with the swim school, we ask that you please give up to 1 month notice. If less than 1 month notice is given, payment for the remaining lessons will be due.

LESSON TIME-

Lessons run according to the schedule. If you arrive late for your lesson, we will only be able to teach you child until the end of their allocated time. In order to avoid this please make sure that: You arrive on time, your child is in their swimsuit, and has used the restroom is needed.

WATCHING LESSONS-

During your students lesson, we ask that you please observe the lessons from a distance. The quality of instruction is often affected by parent and sibling distractions and interruptions, therefore everyone is asked to please remain at a distance until your child is finished with their lesson. If a child is upset or begins to cry, please still remain at a distance. From lots of experience we have found that your child will get used to being in the water with their new instructor faster if left to calm down by themselves.

SICKNESS-

Please do NOT bring children to lessons or the playroom if they are suffering from infections, contagious illness or diseases.

RAIN-

Lessons DO continue if it is raining, whether it is hard or soft rain. The water temperature is nice and warm and the students are already wet when in the water.

POOL DIAPERS-

It is required that ANY students who are not potty trained, wear an elastic swim diaper. Disposable swim diapers can leak into the pool, which forces us to discontinue the lesson until the pool has been properly cleaned for the lessons that will follow. Elastic swim diapers are for sale at the pool for $12.

HAIR-

It is required that any student taking lessons needs to have their hair pulled back and out of their face. Loose hair gets stuck on goggles and in the way while swimming. You are welcome to purchase a swim cap at the pool for $5 as these are the best way to keep hair distractions away from the experience of the lesson.

fields.title: Common Questions
fields.content:
What do bring on my first lesson?

• Towel
• Swim suit
• Sunscreen
• Cash or Check for lessons booked
• Signed liability form for EACH child

What do you do once we arrive at the pool?

• Place the signed liability form in the payment box
• Place any payment amount due in an envelope and in the payment box
• Have the child use the restroom if needed
• Change the child into the swim suit
• Put sunscreen on the child if needed
• Pick out a laminated paper turtle and have your child write their name on it
• Have your child wait in the play area until they are called for their lesson
• Have your child bring their laminated paper turtle into their lesson with them

What do I do once my child is in their swim lesson?

You are welcome to do anything you like as long as you are present BEFORE the child’s lessons time has ended.

What do I do if I am running late?

If possible, call the owner at 1-888-855-SWIM x3 so that they can notify the instructor. Once you do arrive, have your child get ready for their lessons as quickly as possible and then have them hop into the pool for the remaining allocated lesson time. As stated in the rules lessons run according to the schedule. If you arrive late for your lesson, we will only be able to teach you child until the end of their allocated time.

What do I do if my child is upset and does not want to enter the pool?

We do understand that each child is different and some children may be shy or cry about starting swim lessons. We ask that you please walk your child to the pool, introduce them to the instructor and then place them on the steps and walk away. If your child is still upset or begins to cry, please still remain at a distance. From plenty of experience we have found that children will get used to being in the water with their new instructor faster if left to calm down by themselves.

Your question not answered?

Check out the website: www.SeaTurtleSwim.com
Give us a call: 1-888-855-SWIM x3
E-mail us at: candace@seaturtleswim.com info@seaturtleswim.com
